<p>some of their dugouts after they left the penisular, the stuff they threw away as regards food &amp; clothing was scandalous, &amp; hundreds of men in the infantry were in crying need of these articles, where we would have to divide, say 10 cardigans, &amp; 8 pair of socks among 26 men they would have 1 each &amp; sometimes more, &amp; according to the litter left about their dugouts they got the same amount each issue the A.S.C. especially were the ones to rook the Gift's none of the infantry have much time for this branch of the service &amp; vice versa, but I am very pleased to say that this state of things has undergone a drastic alteration of late</p>
